				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Hijacking the Hugos?
				</h2>
				

						
							
							
							
						
						
				<div class="content ">
					<div id="post_message_1833288">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							Apparently, some in the sci-fi community believe that their field's best-known award has been co-opted by right-wing crazies: <br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.slate.com/blogs/browbeat/2015/04/08/_2015_hugo_awards_how_the_sad_and_rabid_puppies_took_over_the_sci_fi_nominations.html" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://www.slate.com/blogs/browbeat/...minations.html</a><br />
<br />
Whether true or not, the fact that it's possible to game the awards in that fashion tells me that the nomination process needs to be overhauled. Fan voting cheapens things.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
