				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Hijacking the Hugos?
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1833304">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>Goladus</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?p=1833303#post1833303" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">Isn't that what a journalist is supposed to do?  Make a reasonable effort to uncover and present the truth?</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>The ideological issues in this instance fail to engage me personally, except to the extent that they underscore weaknesses in the process of choosing one of science fiction's top prizes.<br />
<br />
I like to think I could do a reasonably good job of diving into the issues if I were actually working, but in my case, this is an online forum that's partly a release valve from work. What I do here has about as much resemblance to my professional output as Dmitry's occasional posts on legal matters do to actual court filings.<br />
<br />
Incidentally, ideology aside, Correia also seems to be saying that the nomination procedure itself has flaws. &quot;Haha, look, I can game the system too!&quot;<br />
<br />
But hey, we still have the <a href="https://www.sfwa.org/nebula-awards/how-to-vote/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Nebula Awards</a>!
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
