				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Hijacking the Hugos?
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1833307">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							Correia makes a fundamental error in stating that politics shouldn't matter vs quality of work. For consumers the quality is the enjoyment derived from reading the book. Knowing that the author is a vile bigoted piece of shit like Orson Scott Card might very well make his works unenjoyable, regardless of how pretty the prose or novel the concept. The only way to keep politics out of an awards system would be to keep authors out of political discourse.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
