						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				You cannot judge a work of art in a vacuum. Without personal experience you have no tools to judge it with.
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>By Vacuum I meant judge each work of art on it's own merits not the merits of the &quot;artists&quot; other writings and or comments.   <br />
<br />
<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				By definition art is entwined with politics, because politics are a consequence of the human experience.
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>and by definition a fictional story does not necessarily align with the personal politics of the author.  <br />
<br />
<br />
So let's put it this way...  You dislike Jonathan Swift's A Modest Proposal.  and you disagree with his message.  Because of that - You don't feel that Gulliver's Travels is worthy of any accolades at all, because Jonathan Swift is a Poopy-head.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
