							The issue there is knowing the author's beliefs colours a person's reading of a text. If I know that the author is a racist, I'll examine issues of race in his stories differently than if I did not know that, and possibly reach different conclusions. I could try and examine each text without any knowledge of the author, but unless the author specifically keeps all of their experiences and beliefs out of their work (highly unlikely) this is likely to lead to false conclusions on what the author is trying to say with the work.
						</blockquote>
