		<div class="postbody">
			<div class="postrow has_after_content">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Hijacking the Hugos?
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1833331">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>Melcar</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?p=1833319#post1833319" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">By Vacuum I meant judge each work of art on it's own merits not the merits of the &quot;artists&quot; other writings and or comments.</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>I understand the sentiment, but it's a problem of seeing something you can't un-see. For example - Orson Scott Card's actions have made it nearly impossible for me to enjoy his work. What people say affects perceptions of both them and their work. Separating the two is very difficult and it assumes there's some natural binning process that allows emotional decisions to be made in a logical fashion. That's not really objectively possible.<br />
<br />
<br />
<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				 and by definition a fictional story does not necessarily align with the personal politics of the author.<br />
<br />
So let's put it this way...  You dislike Jonathan Swift's A Modest Proposal.  and you disagree with his message.  Because of that - You don't feel that Gulliver's Travels is worthy of any accolades at all, because Jonathan Swift is a Poopy-head.
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>There's absurdist (Not sure if correct term?) writing and then there's normal writing. A Modest Proposal is absurdist. The author wrote the entire thing to be judged against his political reality. So in fact judging A Modest Proposal in a &quot;vacuum&quot; would completely remove a huge part of its value! Johnathan Swift's politics are incredibly important to the value of A Modest Proposal.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="after_content">
				
                                       
                                 
				
		        		<blockquote class="signature restore"><div class="signaturecontainer">Quelian Spyralshot<br />
<br />
Reach out and <i>Torch</i> someone.</div></blockquote>
				
                                        
			</div>
			
